In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares April 2017 as National Child Abuse Prevention Month. He emphasizes the importance of childhood and the need for children to grow up in loving and safe environments to reach their full potential. The proclamation calls for the prevention of child abuse and neglect and highlights the moral obligation of adults to protect children. The role of strong families and community support is emphasized, as well as the recognition of foster and adoptive parents, child protective workers, and other individuals who work to protect abused or neglected children. The proclamation encourages Americans to be vigilant in ensuring the safety and well-being of children and to support efforts that promote their overall health and development.